recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2023 Bronco and Ranger vehicles.  The lug nuts on the driver's side wheels may have been improperly tightened.
recalls.Consequence: Loose lug nuts may result in wheel detachment while driving, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised not to drive their vehicles until the remedy is completed.  Dealers will inspect, and if necessary, retighten the lug nuts, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed May 2, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S17.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022-2023 Bronco, 2023 Super Duty F-250, and 2019-2023 Ranger vehicles.  The Tire and Loading Information (TREAD) label states the incorrect load carrying capacity, which can result in an overloaded vehicle.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 110, "Tire Selection and Rims."
recalls.Consequence: An overloaded vehicle increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will mail a new TREAD label to install over the existing label, free of charge.  Owners will also have the option to take their vehicle to a Ford or Lincoln dealer to have the new label installed, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 21, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23C18.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2018-2022 Transit Connect, 2019-2020 MKZ, MKX,  Edge, Continental, F-150, Nautilus, Fusion, 2019-2023 Ranger, Mustang, 2020-2021 EcoSport, Expedition, Navigator, 2020-2022 Escape, F-250 SD, Corsair, 2020-2023 Aviator, Transit, 2020-2024 Explorer, 2021-2024 Bronco Sport, and 2022-2024 Maverick vehicles. A software error may cause the rearview camera to display a blank image, or the image may remain on the display after the backing event has ended.
recalls.Consequence: A rearview camera that displays a blank image can reduce the driver's view behind the vehicle. A rearview image that continues to be displayed after the vehicle is shifted out of reverse may distract the driver. Both of these situations can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the rearview camera software, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed September 4, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S72.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2016-2019 Lincoln MKC, 2016-2023 Explorer, 2019-2020 Fusion, 2019-2024 Ranger, 2020-2022 Lincoln Corsair, Escape, 2021-2024 Bronco, Bronco Sport, and 2022-2024 Maverick vehicles. The engine block heater may crack and develop a coolant leak, causing it to short circuit when the block heater is plugged in.
recalls.Consequence: An electrical short circuit can increase the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised not to plug in their block heater until the vehicle is remedied. Dealers will replace the block heater, free of charge. Interim letters, notifying owners of the safety risk, were mailed December 3, 2025. Additional letters will be sent once the final remedy is available, anticipated February 2026. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25SA4. Vehicle Identification Numbers (VINs) involved in this recall became searchable on NHTSA.gov on October 15, 2025.

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Black Screen
issues.description: The SYNC 4A infotainment system randomly freezes, displays a black screen, or becomes unresponsive. This affects navigation, climate controls, and connectivity features.
issues.fix_description: Software update or complete APIM (Accessory Protocol Interface Module) replacement
issues.prevention: Keep software updated and avoid extreme temperature exposure

issues.title: Front Differential Noise and Vibration
issues.description: Excessive noise, clunking, or vibration from the front differential during turns or acceleration, particularly in 4WD mode.
issues.fix_description: Front differential rebuild or replacement, CV joint replacement
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes, avoid aggressive off-road driving

issues.title: Transmission Shifting Issues
issues.description: The 10-speed automatic transmission exhibits harsh shifting, delayed engagement, or slipping between gears.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update, fluid change, or transmission rebuild
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving

issues.title: Paint Defects and Premature Fading
issues.description: Paint quality issues including premature fading, orange peel texture, and poor adhesion, particularly on Code Orange and other bright colors.
issues.fix_description: Panel repainting or full vehicle repaint under warranty
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, garage storage when possible

issues.title: Fox Shock Absorber Leaking
issues.description: Premature leaking of the Fox Racing shocks, causing reduced damping performance and oil stains.
issues.fix_description: Shock absorber replacement under warranty or aftermarket upgrade
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme off-road conditions, regular inspection

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS) Malfunction
issues.description: TPMS sensors provide inaccurate readings or fail to communicate with the vehicle's computer system.
issues.fix_description: TPMS sensor replacement or system reprogramming
issues.prevention: Proper tire maintenance and avoid impact damage

issues.title: Bed Step Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The integrated tailgate step mechanism fails to deploy or retract properly, affecting bed access functionality.
issues.fix_description: Step motor replacement or mechanism repair
issues.prevention: Keep mechanism clean and lubricated, avoid overloading

issues.title: Air Conditioning Performance Issues
issues.description: Inadequate cooling performance, refrigerant leaks, or complete A/C system failure in hot climates.
issues.fix_description: Compressor replacement, refrigerant recharge, or evaporator repair
issues.prevention: Regular A/C service, cabin filter replacement

issues.title: Electronic Parking Brake Malfunction
issues.description: Electronic parking brake fails to engage or disengage properly, potentially causing safety issues.
issues.fix_description: Parking brake actuator replacement or software update
issues.prevention: Regular brake system maintenance, avoid parking on steep grades

issues.title: Interior Trim Rattling and Loose Panels
issues.description: Various interior trim pieces, including dashboard, door panels, and center console, develop rattles or become loose.
issues.fix_description: Trim panel reinstallation with proper clips and adhesives
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, gentle handling of interior components

editorial.tagline: America's Desert Racing Weapon Finally Arrives
editorial.hero_blurb: The Ford Ranger Raptor brings Baja-bred DNA to American shores with a twin-turbo V6 heart. This isn't just a lifted truck—it's a factory-built desert runner that transforms boring commutes into off-road adventures.
editorial.essence: The Ranger Raptor represents Ford's commitment to democratizing high-performance off-roading. Where the F-150 Raptor dominates with brute force, the Ranger Raptor delivers precision and agility through technical terrain.
editorial.heritage: Born from Ford's global Ranger platform and refined through years of international Raptor development, the 2023 model marks the first time Americans get access to this desert-racing legend that's been conquering trails worldwide.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers prioritized functional aggression—every flare, vent, and stance element serves a purpose in extreme off-road conditions while maintaining everyday usability and urban maneuverability.
editorial.motorsport_history: Developed alongside Ford's Ranger racing program, incorporating lessons learned from Dakar Rally competition and Baja 1000 endurance racing into production-ready technology.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.0L twin-turbo V6 EcoBoost delivers instant torque with a sophisticated growl, building power linearly from low RPMs with an addictive whoosh from the turbos under load.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 10-speed automatic shifts with purpose, holding gears intelligently in off-road modes while delivering smooth, quick shifts on pavement with well-spaced ratios.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Fox Racing shocks and reinforced frame create a truck that soaks up whoops and jumps while maintaining surprising composure on twisty pavement, though it favors capability over ultimate refinement.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and well-weighted for a truck this capable, offering good feedback through technical terrain while remaining relaxed enough for highway cruising without excessive corrections.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive braking with good pedal feel and fade resistance, though the truck's weight and off-road focus means it won't match sports car precision.
editorial.sound_signature: A muscular V6 rumble punctuated by turbo whoosh and subtle exhaust bark—more sophisticated than a V8's roar but still distinctly purposeful and engaging.
editorial.ideal_owner: Adventure-seeking enthusiasts who need genuine off-road capability without F-150 Raptor's size penalty, plus weekend warriors who value capability over luxury.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum towing capacity, luxury truck refinement, or those who'll never venture beyond pavement—this truck's talents deserve to be used.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Ranger Raptor delivers authentic off-road performance in a more manageable package than its F-150 sibling. It's the thinking enthusiast's choice for serious trail capability with daily driving practicality.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Ford Ranger Raptor REVIEW Is It The BEST Pickup Truck?
pros: 405 horsepower twin-turbo V6
Very comfortable seats with bolstering support
Good visibility and maneuverability
Excellent off-road capabilities with multiple drive modes
Nice interior materials and Bang & Olufsen sound system
Paddle shifters and responsive performance
cons: Lower towing capacity compared to non-Raptor (5,500 lbs)
High MSRP at just shy of $58,000
Poor fuel economy at 16 city/18 highway MPG
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford Ranger Raptor is described as basically an F-150 Raptor in smaller form. It offers good daily driving comfort, strong performance with 405hp, and excellent off-road capabilities. The reviewer notes it's well-designed for taller people and would make a great daily driver. However, the high price point and reduced towing capacity are notable drawbacks. It's positioned as a good alternative for those who want Raptor performance but don't need a full-size truck.

expertReviews.title: New 2025 Ford Ranger Raptor Review | Can An Off-road Toy Also Be Daily Driver?
pros: Amazing drivetrain with 292hp V6
Excellent off-road capability - keeps up with closest rivals
Comfortable suspension for all situations
Great practicality with multiple storage options
Single-minded focus on off-road performance
Playful and fun to drive
Impressive styling with Baja pre-runner inspiration
cons: Poor fuel economy at 19 MPG combined
Road tire drone at highway speeds
Limited rear seat space for adults
Compromised towing capacity at only 2.5 tons
Heavy at 2.5 tons affects performance
expertReviews.verdict: The Ford Ranger Raptor is described as 'the coolest vehicle currently on sale' - a single-minded off-road focused pickup that's slightly compromised but excellently executed. With 292hp, impressive off-road capability rivaling the Jeep Rubicon, and comfortable suspension, it works as both a fun toy and daily driver despite fuel economy and practicality compromises.

expertReviews.title: The Ford Ranger Raptor is ALMOST Perfect - Owner Review
pros: Excellent size and maneuverability compared to full-size trucks
Outstanding suspension performance at speed
Great balance and fun factor for off-roading
Excellent air conditioning system
Spacious rear seats for midsize segment
Advanced cruise control with lane keeping
Works well as both daily driver and off-road toy
Ford Performance ProCal tune adds significant power
cons: Turbo lag even with tune
Limited storage compared to F-150
Lacks premium features available on F-150 (bed cam, AC seats, sunroof options)
Cheaper interior materials and tactile feel
Small 20.3 gallon fuel tank
Electronic mirrors don't sync with seat memory positions
Center hump affects rear passenger comfort
expertReviews.verdict: Brandon calls the 2025 Ford Ranger Raptor 'almost perfect' after 8-9 months of ownership. While it excels as both a capable off-roader and practical daily driver with superior maneuverability over full-size trucks, it's held back by Ford's strategy of keeping it a tier below the F-150 in terms of features and interior quality. The truck delivers on fun factor and utility but suffers from turbo lag and storage limitations.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Ford Ranger Raptor - Brutally Honest 1-Year Ownership
pros: Dominates every off-road environment
Super comfortable on pothole roads
Excellent infotainment system responsiveness
Great seats with supportive bolstering
Reliable with minimal issues over one year
Versatile daily driver and family hauler
Excellent climate control
Good ergonomics and interior storage
cons: Poor fuel economy (14-15 MPG average)
Rear diff underfilled from factory
Initial wet traction dangerous with KO3 tires
Lane centering automatically engages with cruise control
No ventilated seats
Hood difficult to shut properly
Expensive fuel consumption
expertReviews.verdict: After one year of ownership, the 2024 Ford Ranger Raptor proves to be an excellent off-road capable truck that serves well as both a daily driver and adventure vehicle. Despite poor fuel economy and some minor issues like underfilled diff fluid from factory, the truck has been reliable and dominates in all environments from sand dunes to ice racing. The infotainment system works well, seats are comfortable, and it handles family duties effectively while maintaining serious off-road capability.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Ford Ranger Raptor Review - INCREDIBLE For The ...
pros: Excellent value at $59,000
More powerful than competitors like Tacoma TRD Pro
Better fuel economy (18.5 mpg vs 16.5 in Tacoma)
Comfortable seats with good back seat space
Runs on 87 octane fuel
Great customizable driving modes
Most affordable Raptor option
cons: Not stellar fuel economy overall
Manual tailgate (no power operation)
Knees hit front seats in back row
expertReviews.verdict: One of the best trucks in the midsize segment. At $59,000, it offers exceptional value compared to competitors, with more power, better fuel economy, and superior comfort. Only $7,000 more than average American vehicle price while delivering significantly more capability. Highly recommended unless 8-ft bed or maximum towing are priorities.

expertReviews.title: Ford Ranger Raptor HONEST REVIEW by Jeep Gladiator Owner
pros: More nimble and compact than F-150 Raptor while maintaining similar power
Excellent seat bolstering and comfort with Alcantara accents
Good power options including 405hp standard, 450hp with dealer tune
Practical size - 6 inches wider than regular Ranger but still manageable for parking
Quality interior materials and multiple power outlets for camping/adventure use
Can fit 34-35 inch tires on stock 8.5 inch wide wheels
Matrix LED headlight capability via software unlock
cons: Plastic skid plate on gas tank instead of aluminum
Rear seat space is tight compared to F-150
Obnoxious Raptor graphics (owner's opinion)
Side steps aren't true sliders and will bend
expertReviews.verdict: The Ranger Raptor impresses as a more manageable alternative to the F-150 Raptor, offering similar power (405hp standard, 450hp with dealer tune) in a more compact package. The reviewer, a Jeep Gladiator owner, was particularly impressed with the seat comfort, interior quality with Alcantara accents, and the truck's nimble handling. While it has some compromises like tight rear seating and a plastic fuel tank skid plate, it delivers the Raptor experience in a more city-friendly size that's still capable off-road.
